---
// WhatJustHappened.astro
// Concrete walkthrough of what the demo showed
---

<section class="section reveal" id="what-happened">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="what-happened">
      <h2 class="what-happened__title">What just happened</h2>
      <div class="what-happened__body">
        <p>
          A coordination contract was assembled from content-addressed registry artefacts — a schema
          defining the allowed output structure, a guardian policy providing defense in depth, and a
          prompt program governing the model interaction. Each artefact is identified by its SHA-256
          digest.
        </p>
        <p>
          The relay admitted only artefacts whose digests matched its registry index — fail-closed
          by default. Both agents submitted private context. Neither saw the other's raw input.
        </p>
        <p>
          The relay assembled the prompt, called the model, and validated the output against the
          JSON Schema. Anything that did not conform was rejected, not returned. The guardian policy
          applied a second enforcement layer — for example, blocking raw numerics and currency
          symbols in string fields.
        </p>
        <p>
          The result: a <strong>bounded signal</strong> — a compressed, schema-constrained output —
          not a conversation or free-text summary.
        </p>
        <p>
          A signed receipt (v2) was produced with two sections: <strong>commitments</strong>
          (cryptographically verifiable — contract hash, schema hash, input commitment hashes,
          output) and <strong>claims</strong> (relay-asserted — model identity, token usage,
          latency). The distinction makes explicit what a verifier can check independently.
        </p>
        <p>
          Raw inputs were discarded after receipt construction. Only commitment hashes persist.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .what-happened {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .what-happened__title {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .what-happened__body p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .what-happened__body p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
</style>
